75. Sort Colors
Problem

Given an array containing only:

0 → Red
1 → White
2 → Blue

Sort the array in-place such that:

All 0s come first,
then 1s,
then 2s.

Without using:

Arrays.sort()
Optimal Approach — Dutch National Flag Algorithm
Intuition

Use 3 pointers:

low  → position for next 0
mid  → current element
high → position for next 2

The array is divided into 4 regions:

0 to low-1      → all 0s
low to mid-1    → all 1s
mid to high     → unsorted
high+1 to end   → all 2s
Algorithm
If nums[mid] == 0

0 should go to left side.

Swap:

nums[low] ↔ nums[mid]

Move:

low++
mid++
If nums[mid] == 1

1 is already in correct position.

Move:

mid++
If nums[mid] == 2

2 should go to right side.

Swap:

nums[mid] ↔ nums[high]

Move:

high--

Do NOT increment mid because swapped element must be checked again.

Dry Run
Input
nums = [2,0,2,1,1,0]

Initial pointers:

low = 0
mid = 0
high = 5
Step 1
nums[mid] = 2

Swap mid and high:

[0,0,2,1,1,2]
high--
Step 2
nums[mid] = 0

Swap low and mid:

[0,0,2,1,1,2]
low++
mid++
Step 3
nums[mid] = 0

Swap again.

low++
mid++
Step 4
nums[mid] = 2

Swap with high:

[0,0,1,1,2,2]
high--
Step 5
nums[mid] = 1
mid++
Final Output
[0,0,1,1,2,2]
Java Code
class Solution {
    public void sortColors(int[] nums) {

        int low = 0;
        int mid = 0;
        int high = nums.length - 1;

        while(mid <= high) {

            if(nums[mid] == 0) {

                int temp = nums[low];
                nums[low] = nums[mid];
                nums[mid] = temp;

                low++;
                mid++;
            }

            else if(nums[mid] == 1) {

                mid++;
            }

            else {

                int temp = nums[mid];
                nums[mid] = nums[high];
                nums[high] = temp;

                high--;
            }
        }
    }
}
Complexity Analysis
Time Complexity
O(n)

Each element is processed at most once.

Space Complexity
O(1)

No extra space used.

Important Interview Points
Why do we not increment mid when nums[mid] == 2?

After swapping with high, the new element at mid may be:

0 or 1 or 2

So it must be checked again.

Key Pattern
3 Pointer Partitioning

Also known as:

Dutch National Flag Algorithm
